Step-by-Step: Create Branches in GitHub
Step 1 — Clone repository
git clone https://github.com/your-org/lms-app.git
cd lms-app
Step 2 — Create develop branch (QA environment)
git checkout -b develop
git push origin develop

This branch deploys to QA.

Step 3 — Create release branch (UAT environment)
git checkout -b release/v1.0
git push origin release/v1.0

This branch deploys to UAT.

Step 4 — main branch already exists (PROD)
git checkout main
git push origin main

This branch deploys to PROD.

Step 5 — Create feature branch (DEV environment)

Example:

git checkout develop
git checkout -b feature/course-module
git push origin feature/course-module

This branch deploys to DEV.

